snippet: Newly released data show that many commercial stocks depleted by overfishing are returning in abundance since a 1996 law that effectively ordered limits on catches.
abstract: Natural Resources Defense Council data finds many commercial fishing stocks off United States coast depleted by decades of overfishing are returning to abundance, largely due to1996 law that effectively ordered limits on catches until fish populations had rebounded.
lead_paragraph: Newly released data show that many commercial stocks depleted by overfishing are returning in abundance since a 1996 law that effectively ordered limits on catches.

headline.seo: Fish Populations Rebound Since 1996 Catch-Limits Law
headline.main: Fish Populations in the United States Rebound
